title: Grateful Dead Live at Kiel Auditorium on 1973-10-29
description:
Set 1

Cold Rain & Snow, Beat It On Down The Line, Brown Eyed Women, Mexicali Blues, Don't Ease Me In, Black Throated Wind, Tennessee Jed, The Race is On, Row Jimmy, El Paso, Eyes Of The World-> China Doll, Around & Around

Set 2

Promised Land-> Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Loser, Big River, Brokedown Palace, Truckin'-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Casey Jones

reviews.review_text: Casey Jones Really nice to have the encore for this one....
Too much audience for a matrix This is incredibly hissy and sounds more like an audience recording than a matrix.  I think a better balance between sources could have been achieved.
Great Blend of SBD and AUD Feels like I am actually at this show, thank you for this Matrix, the original SBD sound incredibly flat and dull compared to this. Fun and explorative show.

Last 7 min of Other One First the mix. I'm not sure what is up here. There are parts of this that are one of the best sound MTXs I've ever heard, and then others when it does in fact sound like a C- AUD. Still other parts are somewhere in-between. Go figure. 

This show is loaded, big time. Someone tells you otherwise and you can just discount their opinions from now on. They were so on point in fall 73 it can be hard to believe some times. Pretty much everything is at least very solid. 

Truckin is wonderfully aggressive and nailed through the song section. After a short bit Phil takes control and leads them way out over the horizon. This would be one of those when Billy probably had to stop and try to recall what song they were playing. 

What matters though, the Other One is solid enough for 15 minutes, then it transcends the heavens. Grateful Dead magic at its very best...led by Keith. And fortunately, the mix for TOO is perfection. And the following Wharf Rat is very tasty. 

The Eyes> China Doll is indeed one of the very best you'll ever hear. Also, the Brokedown Palace...oh god. But for Phjl's harmonizing attempts this is spine tinglingly great. Jerry's voice is crackling and his solo is the very stuff of life. 

4 stars for inconsistent mix.
